Method Detail

checkConnection

public boolean checkConnection()
Checks whether the connection is still alive. Unspecific things to do can be put into this method (see commented region). Note: The connection can fail also temporarily. But often enough, it will not be re-established.

Returns:
whether or not the connection is currently alive

connect

pulseSign - a character used to display the network pulse

whether the connection could be established
See Also:
to close the connection

actuallySend

public AgentNetworker.SendStatus actuallySend(java.lang.String str)
Does the actual (technical side of the) sending. The socket will be opened for writing, and closed after the EMBRScript is delivered.

send

public AgentNetworker.SendStatus send(java.lang.String script,
                                      boolean timed)
Sends the pose sequence to the agent. Usually, a timer is invoked to determine whether the send should be instantly carried out, or rather be scheduled for delivery on the next tick. The timer shall prevent network traffic overload and socket.

Parameters:
script - The EMBRScript to be sent
timed - whether the timer should be used
Returns:
status message
